NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Although 2N by Cheryl is certainly reasonable, since she has a diamond stopper I think 3C is another possibility since her club suit is so good. It is basically self sufficient. That means it passes the "singleton test", meaning it plays well opposite a singleton. In fact, even if Vered has a void, Cheryl most likely has only 1 club loser (if clubs split 4-3).|
