^-|CP||FP||ht|c|at|^B@2^Z@3Bridge information stays with me as long as writing on the sand at the beach. It takes only one soft wave to wash everything away. However, as I get older I become more persistent and keep writing on the sand--reviewing the material over and over. This week I have several points that I have heard them from Howard many times, know them by heart but forget to use them when at a bridge table. Nothing new of course.|
