ht|g|va|4|CP|4|CS|1|AT|^-{    FOR DECLARER    }
^-|CP||CS||AT|
^BWhen you plan to trump losers in dummy, it might be necessary to delay drawing trump to ensure having enough trumps left in dummy to do the job.|
PG| ***** 120 ***** |


AT|

Draw trump immediately unless you have a very good reason - like ruffing losers in dummy. It never hurts to play it safe whenever you can.|
PG| ***** 121 ***** |


AT|

Remember that the opponents can lead trump too.|
PG| ***** 122 ***** |


AT|

Evaluate the distribution of the suit you are ruffing. You may have to to trump high to avoid an overruff.|
PG| ***** 123 ***** |


AT|

Between taking a finesse or trumping in dummy to make your contract, do the ruffing. Finesses only work half the time you know.|
PG| ***** 124 ***** |


AT|

Be prepared to revise your original plan to cope with something unexpected like a bad trump split.|
PG| ***** 125 ***** |


AT|

What's good for declarer is bad for the opponents. Trumping in dummy is good for declarer. It's usually best for the opponents to avoid leading a suit that dummy can trump.|
PG| ***** 126 ***** |


AT|

The opponents should lead trump when they see a short suit in dummy. Trumping in declarer's hand is not usually good for declarer. The opponents usually should not fear leading a suit that declarer can trump.|
